  "text": "Also analysed in each of the interviews were three evidence disclosure modes. 'Early' would reflect the interviewer revealing of all the evidence held before an initial account had been requested. 'Gradual' disclosing of the evidence involved a 'drip-feed' approach during the questioning phase of the interview (as in [CITATION_1] . 'Late' disclosure would be so classified when the questioning strategy was characterised by the asking for an account (that was subsequently probed) but the evidence held was not revealed until the interviewer appeared to consider that all potential alibis and topics had been covered.",
